item.description:
 &lt;h1 id=&#34;two-level-atom&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#two-level-atom&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Two-Level Atom&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;rabi-oscillation&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#rabi-oscillation&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Rabi oscillation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;katex-mathml&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mspace width=&#34;1em&#34;&gt;&lt;/mspace&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\quad&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;katex-html&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;base&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;strut&#34; style=&#34;height:0em;vertical-align:0em;&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mspace&#34; style=&#34;margin-right:1em;&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; The two-level system is an elementary but basic tool in quantum optics. &lt;a href=&#34;../%E9%AB%98%E7%AD%89%E5%8E%9F%E5%AD%90%E5%88%86%E5%AD%90%E7%89%A9%E7%90%86/%E7%AC%AC1%E7%AB%A0%20%E5%AD%A4%E7%AB%8B%E4%BA%8C%E8%83%BD%E7%BA%A7%E5%8E%9F%E5%AD%90%E8%B7%83%E8%BF%81.md&#34;&gt;In the previous note&lt;/a&gt;, we have discussed the interaction of a two-level atom with a classical field. Here, let&#39;s review this topic again with more concise symbols and new understandings.&lt;br&gt;
